description.narrative: The development objectives of the project are to: (a) improve the enabling environment for the telecommunications sector and extend coverage in selected remote pilot locations; and (b) establish priority eGovernment technological foundations and institutional capacity for Government to embark on its public sector reform program.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Annual work plans and budgets | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to prepare for IDA’s approval annualwork plans and budgets for the Project, two months before the beginning of each fiscal year starting February 2015. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Environmental and Social Safeguards: | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to carry out the Project inaccordance with the ESMF and related safeguard assessments and plans | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Maintenance of Project Steering Committee and MCIT Project implementation team | Description :Section I.A,Schedule 2: Obligation of the Recipient to maintain the Project Steering Committee and MCIT Project implementation team at alltimes during the implementation of the Project | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Pilot rural extension subprojects | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to ensure that all pilot ruraltelecommunications service extension subprojects under Component 2 are carried out in accordance with agreed eligibility criteria,terms and conditions and approval and administration arrangements | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Project implementation manual | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to carry out the Project in accordancewith the Project Implementation Manual | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Project midterm | Description :Obligation of the Recipient and IDA to conduct the midterm review of the project.| Due Date :31-Oct-2016

Finance Agreement :Project reports and IFRs | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to submit quarterly project progress reportsand interim unaudited financial reports within 45 days after each quarter. | Frequency :Quarterly
